        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1960-03-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="[Unnumbered document following Document 710 (#53)]" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d710a-53">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Editor’s Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>—No official record of the substance of this conversation has been found.
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL2">Stimson</persName>’s diary entry for July 21
                    contains the following summary: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I then left the ‘Little White House’, picked up <persName corresp="#p_BHH1">Bundy</persName>, and went to the Prime Minister’s
                            house where we conferred with him and <persName corresp="#p_CL1">Lord
                                Cherwell</persName>. I turned over the paper<note n="1" xml:id="d710a-53fn1">
                                <ref target="#d1305">Document No. 1305</ref>, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>.</note> to <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName> and he began reading it but was interrupted a
                            few minutes before five in order to hurry to the Big Three Conference at
                            five o’clock. He asked me to return on the following morning to finish
                            up the report.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
